-- Development Bank of Southern Africa Says First-Half Net Profit Tumbles 97%
-- B y   P a u l   R i c h a r d s o n
-- 2010-11-29T05:04:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-29/development-bank-of-southern-africa-says-first-half-net-profit-tumbles-97-.html
Development Bank of Southern Africa
Ltd., a state-owned lender, said first-half profit plunged 97
percent.  Net income dropped to 6.51 million rand ($910,642) in the
six months through September, from 236.2 million rand a year
earlier, the company said in a statement published in the
Johannesburg-based Business Day newspaper today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net  